  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community Stabilization Index (COSI) in Middle Shabelle</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Community Stabilization Index (COSI) is a statistical tool based on a set of weighted metrics to assess how stability is understood locally. Based on this, the project seeks to gain fine-grained knowledge of the profiles of areas where different stakeholders interact and highlight key factors influencing community stabilization in Middle Shabelle, Somalia. Within the framework of this project, the activity entails household data collection using a perception survey deployed to four target locations in Middle Shabelle. COSI collects data on five themes including Community Recovery, Rule of Law, Social Cohesion &amp; Reconciliation, Local Governance, and Population Movement. This project supports the implementation of data-informed community stabilization activities in the region.</narrative>
  </description>
